<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8c073f0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8126"><num value="8126">§ 8126.</num><heading> Subpenas; oaths; examination of witnesses</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Labor, on any matter within his jurisdiction under this subchapter, may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c073f1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8126/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> issue subpenas for and compel the attendance of witnesses within a radius of 100 miles;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c073f2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8126/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> administer oaths;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c073f3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8126/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> examine witnesses; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c073f4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8126/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> require the production of books, papers, documents, and other evidence.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb8c073f5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/554">Pub. L. 89–554</ref>, <date date="1966-09-06">Sept. 6, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/545">80 Stat. 545</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
